            "date": "2020-08-11 23:51:33.000000000",
            "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI've been running this for hours now and haven't seen a deadlock yet. I also poked against the wsgi server a lot and didn't get it to leak any workers (although I wasn't making requests). I'm wondering if the masking of signals during the SIGHUP handling means it's just missing our SIGTERM occasionally or something, and my previous patch to kill the children was sometimes doing so in an order that caused an orphan to be reparented. I will still keep poking on that, but this seems to make the tests not lock up for me.",
            "accounts_in_message": [],
            "_revision_number": 1
        },
